# INDEX.md — repo map

**Copy this to your project root. It is the file Claude reads first to understand the codebase.**

Keep it under 80 lines. It is a *map*, not documentation.

---

## Top-level layout

| Path | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `src/` | Application source. Entry point at `src/index.ts`. |
| `tests/` | Test suites. One file per source module. Pattern: `tests/<module>.test.ts`. |
| `scripts/` | One-off operational scripts. Run with `npm run <name>`. |
| `infra/` | Infrastructure-as-code. Terraform / Pulumi / Wrangler configs. |
| `docs/` | Reader-facing documentation (not for Claude). Architecture decisions, API reference. |

## Key modules

| Module | Entry | Owner |
|---|---|---|
| Auth | `src/auth/index.ts` | [team] |
| Billing | `src/billing/index.ts` | [team] |
| Data layer | `src/db/index.ts` | [team] |

## Critical commands

| Task | Command |
|---|---|
| Install | `npm install` |
| Dev server | `npm run dev` |
| Tests | `npm test` |
| Typecheck | `npm run typecheck` |
| Lint | `npm run lint` |
| Build | `npm run build` |
| Deploy (staging) | `npm run deploy:staging` |
| Deploy (production) | `npm run deploy` (gated, requires approval) |

## Gotchas

- Secrets in `.env`. Never read out; never write. Reference `.env.example` for shape.
- Database migrations live in `infra/migrations/`. Never edit a committed migration; always add a new one.
- Production deploy requires the `OPERATOR` role.

